  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Emergency Assistance for the Healthcare System of Ukraine</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">After six years of conflict, the situation in eastern Ukraine remains volatile. Although 2019 witnessed some positive steps, the protracted crisis in eastern Ukraine is leaving serious consequences, with daily hostilities affecting civilians and military service personnel, damaging critical infrastructure and often disrupting essential services. The incidents caused by the conflict produced a growing need for special type of diagnostic and surgeries, which the state has limited resources to address with the multitude of humanitarian and peace process related issues it needs to tackle. 

With funding from the government of Japan, UNOPS offers emergency assistance for the healthcare system of Ukraine through procurement support of three X-ray systems and of one neurosurgical operating microscope for Military Medical Clinical Centres in the country. 

The beneficiaries include approximately 40,060 patients per year benefiting from the enhanced treatment, and approximately 290 medical personnel in the Department of the Military Medical Clinical Centres working with modernised equipment and in better conditions.</narrative>
  </description>
